 CheckKeyBehaviors(), CheckVirtualMods(), CheckKeyExplicit(), and
 CheckVirtualModMap() loop over client request data without performing
 adequate bound checking. A specially crafted request can cause these
 functions to read past the request data bounds, leading to out-of-bounds
 memory access. Add _XkbCheckRequestBounds() calls to validate that the
 data remains within the request bounds before accessing it.
